<title>BEYBLADE UNIVERSE</title>
<body>
    <p>Definition: Beyblade Burst is the third generation of the popular Beyblade spinning top franchise, launched by Takara
    Tomy in 2015.<br>
    Core Mechanic: It introduced a "Burst" feature where tops can break apart into pieces upon intense impact, adding an
    extra way to win.<br>
    Components: Each top consists of three main parts: an Energy Layer, a Forge Disc, and a Performance Tip.<br>
    Battle Conditions: Players aim to win by either a "Burst Finish" (2 points), "Survivor Finish" (1 point), or "Ring Out
    Finish" (1 point), usually reaching 3 points first.
    Types: Beyblades come in four main types—Attack, Stamina, Defense, and Balance—each with unique performance
    characteristics.<br>
    Launcher System: Players use specialized launchers, often with strings or ripcords, to release the tops into a
    Beystadium.<br>
    Customization: Components are interchangeable, allowing players to create custom combinations to optimize for specific
    battle strategies.<br>
    Media Tie-in: The toy line is supported by an anime series, which follows characters like Valt Aoi as they aim to become
    the world's best Blader.<br>
    Tournament Scene: Beyblade Burst has a strong competitive scene, with local and international tournaments hosted by the
    World Beyblade Organization.<br>
    Digital Integration: Many tops include a code that can be scanned into the Beyblade Burst app for digital battles and
    virtual collection.</p>
